# Abashevo, Chuvash Republic

}}
Abashevo (; , Apa≈ü) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Abashevskoye Rural Settlement of Cheboksarsky District, Chuvash Republic, Russia. The population was 851 as of 2012. There are 9 streets.
Geography
Abashevo is located on the left bank of the Ryksha River, 7 km southeast of Kugesi (the district's administrative centre) by road. Zavrazhnoye is the nearest rural locality.
